1
00:00:10,916 --> 00:00:11,916
[HOKO]
Reiko.

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,500
Uh, yes, ma'am?

3
00:00:15,291 --> 00:00:17,916
Your marriage talks have
officially concluded.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:19,625
[gasps]

5
00:00:19,708 --> 00:00:21,416
If you abandon me and the
rest of the Commoner Club,

6
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:23,250
I don't know what I'll do!

7
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:26,375
[REIKO]
I want to stay at Seikain.

8
00:00:26,458 --> 00:00:29,875
I wanna stay there with
Hakua, and with Karen.

9
00:00:29,958 --> 00:00:33,750
And most of all, I want
to stay with you, Aika.

10
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:38,416
I'm so scared. Please,
I've no idea what to do.

11
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:40,625
[AIKA] Don't worry.
We'll think of something.

12
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,208
One way or another, we
will get you out of this.

13
00:00:45,291 --> 00:00:47,000
[KIMITO]
It's all right.

14
00:00:47,083 --> 00:00:49,208
This is a job for a Commoner.

15
00:02:31,166 --> 00:02:34,083
We're out of the woods
now, for the most part.

16
00:02:34,166 --> 00:02:37,666
Hey. Why'd you turn to us?

17
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,750
I'm a member of
the Arisugawa family.

18
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:43,291
I can't very well be seen
to be against the engagement.

19
00:02:43,375 --> 00:02:46,333
My sister's fate rests
entirely in your hands.

20
00:02:52,375 --> 00:02:55,458
So, is this what a
real city looks like?

21
00:02:55,541 --> 00:02:57,916
It resembles
Shominland remarkably.

22
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,666
[KIMITO]
You've got that backwards.

23
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,083
[KIMITO]
What's the matter?

24
00:03:07,166 --> 00:03:08,416
[MASAOMI]
See for yourself.

25
00:03:10,458 --> 00:03:11,875
[KIMITO]
That's a lot of security.

26
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:13,583
[AIKA]
Lemme see, lemme see!

27
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:14,958
This is bad.

28
00:03:15,041 --> 00:03:16,166
Somebody talked to my mother,

29
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:18,375
which means we have
a leak on the inside.

30
00:03:18,458 --> 00:03:21,208
[AIKA]
Whoa! They have wooden swords!

31
00:03:21,291 --> 00:03:22,416
What do we do now?

32
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:23,625
Here's the deal.

33
00:03:23,708 --> 00:03:25,291
You charge in there
and create a diversion.

34
00:03:25,375 --> 00:03:26,708
While the guards are distracted,

35
00:03:26,791 --> 00:03:29,000
I'll slip past them and
make my way inside the house.

36
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:31,541
No way! I'm not
chargin' in there!

37
00:03:33,541 --> 00:03:34,875
[KAREN]
Aika's right.

38
00:03:34,958 --> 00:03:36,375
Those men are wielding swords.

39
00:03:36,458 --> 00:03:39,041
And from the looks of it,
they're quite handy with them.

40
00:03:40,375 --> 00:03:43,000
It's time. My time.

41
00:03:43,083 --> 00:03:45,750
The moment I've been waiting
for my whole life is here.

42
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:48,875
I will fight these swordsmen and
put my training to the test!

43
00:03:48,958 --> 00:03:50,458
We have to get to Reiko.

44
00:03:50,541 --> 00:03:52,083
And I'm guessing
the only way to do it

45
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:53,375
is through that front gate.

46
00:03:53,458 --> 00:03:54,875
Yeah. That's right.

47
00:03:54,958 --> 00:03:55,791
Karen, wait.

48
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:58,250
No. I'm done waiting.

49
00:03:58,333 --> 00:03:59,791
This is my chance!

50
00:04:06,458 --> 00:04:08,250
My name is Karen Jinyo!

51
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:12,000
I challenge all of you to a
fight to the death by sword.

52
00:04:12,083 --> 00:04:15,291
Karen style sword art!
Resolution!

53
00:04:16,375 --> 00:04:17,833
[GUARDS yell]

54
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:26,708
Oh no. Where're my compatriots?

55
00:04:26,791 --> 00:04:29,833
That Kimito never was much
for sticking to the plan.

56
00:04:29,916 --> 00:04:33,541
Regardless, today is the day
I show the world my quality.

57
00:04:33,625 --> 00:04:37,458
Behold my new technique!
Karen style sword art!

58
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:39,166
Single Stretch!

59
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:53,125
And we're in!

60
00:04:53,208 --> 00:04:55,250
Wow! That was some straight
up superhero stuff!

61
00:04:55,333 --> 00:04:57,208
We better go while we still can!

62
00:04:59,458 --> 00:05:01,541
Oh no! We're surrounded!

63
00:05:03,666 --> 00:05:05,291
Looks like it's
the end of the line.

64
00:05:05,375 --> 00:05:08,333
There's too many, Kimito,
we don't stand a chance!

65
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:12,583
[KAREN] Continue the
mission. I'll handle them.

66
00:05:12,666 --> 00:05:14,541
Right! My sister thanks you!

67
00:05:14,625 --> 00:05:15,833
[KIMITO]
Be careful!

68
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:17,833
Karen style sword art.

69
00:05:17,916 --> 00:05:21,583
Whirlwind Number 58.
Overabundance!

70
00:05:27,291 --> 00:05:29,208
[TAKEMIYA]
Not so fast, Master Masaomi.

71
00:05:29,291 --> 00:05:31,041
Please, let us by!

72
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:32,666
You know I can't do that.

73
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:35,208
I recognize this must
be very hard on you.

74
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:38,208
But Master Masaomi, it's
time to let your sister go!

75
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:39,916
I will not!

76
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,333
What're you doing?

77
00:05:41,416 --> 00:05:44,458
Takemiya!

78
00:05:46,416 --> 00:05:48,750
[TAKEMIYA]
I see your resolve is strong.

79
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:50,750
But it's not strong enough.

80
00:05:53,458 --> 00:05:55,333
[MASAOMI] Don't worry,
guys, I'll handle him!

81
00:05:55,416 --> 00:05:58,166
You go on ahead without me!

82
00:05:58,250 --> 00:06:03,250
[yelling]

83
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:07,375
Quickly!

84
00:06:07,458 --> 00:06:08,958
Reiko's up the stairs
and to the right.

85
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:10,500
[KIMITO]
Good work, Hakua.

86
00:06:10,583 --> 00:06:12,041
[AIKA]
Hold on, Kimito!

87
00:06:12,125 --> 00:06:14,166
Slow down a bit!
I think I'm gonna puke!

88
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:16,000
How can you say that
at a time like this?

89
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:17,583
[AIKA]
Because I'm gonna puke!

90
00:06:20,916 --> 00:06:24,083
First we had to deal with
guards. And now robots?

91
00:06:25,541 --> 00:06:27,875
[AIKA]
I can handle this one.

92
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:29,166
[KIMITO]
Handle it how?

93
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:40,291
[yelling]

94
00:06:43,416 --> 00:06:45,083
Where'd you learn
to throw like that?

95
00:06:45,166 --> 00:06:46,500
[AIKA chuckles]

96
00:06:46,583 --> 00:06:48,250
Pretty impressive
don't'cha think?

97
00:06:48,333 --> 00:06:49,041
[HAKUA]
Keep moving!

98
00:06:49,125 --> 00:06:50,000
[KIMITO]
Right!

99
00:06:50,083 --> 00:06:50,875
[AIKA gasps]

100
00:06:50,958 --> 00:06:52,458
[AIKA]
Hey! Wait for me!

101
00:06:54,916 --> 00:06:56,083
[bang]

102
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:58,041
The hell is this?

103
00:06:58,125 --> 00:06:59,333
[KIMITO]
Oh, crap!

104
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:01,666
[HAKUA] Come on! The
control room's right here!

105
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:03,000
[KIMITO]
Good job, Hakua!

106
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,333
[KIMITO]
Look out!

107
00:07:09,416 --> 00:07:10,458
[AIKA]
Are you okay?

108
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:11,541
We're good.

109
00:07:11,625 --> 00:07:12,666
Thanks a lot.

110
00:07:16,916 --> 00:07:20,041
It's closing too quickly!

111
00:07:20,125 --> 00:07:23,541
We aren't gonna make it!

112
00:07:26,458 --> 00:07:27,875
I love muscles.

113
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:37,041
Hakua, you're almost there!

114
00:07:53,666 --> 00:07:55,041
Hot damn, it worked!

115
00:08:00,416 --> 00:08:03,041
Kimito, what're you standing
around like that for?

116
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:04,291
We gotta move!

117
00:08:04,375 --> 00:08:05,333
My bad!

118
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:09,958
[KIMITO]
Hakua, is this the right way?

119
00:08:10,041 --> 00:08:12,000
[HAKUA]
Yeah. Just past this room.

120
00:08:13,416 --> 00:08:14,458
[AIKA]
This way?

121
00:08:16,875 --> 00:08:18,916
[AIKA]
Is that what I think it is?

122
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:23,375
Hakua, how do we
stop this thing?

123
00:08:26,583 --> 00:08:27,125
[AIKA yelps]

124
00:08:27,208 --> 00:08:28,500
Watch out!

125
00:08:28,583 --> 00:08:29,666
[ALL gasp]

126
00:08:36,208 --> 00:08:38,125
[KAREN]
Sorry to keep you waiting.

127
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:39,625
Is everybody all right?

128
00:08:39,708 --> 00:08:41,750
Karen! Where did you
get that outfit?

129
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:43,416
There's a room in this mansion.

130
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,500
It's flow of time is different
from the outside world's.

131
00:08:46,583 --> 00:08:47,750
That sounds cool.

132
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:49,458
Uh! Be careful!

133
00:08:50,958 --> 00:08:52,916
[KAREN]
Watch and learn, Kagurazaka!

134
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,541
This is not Resolution.

135
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:56,916
Nor Overabundance,
nor Single Stretch!

136
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:00,708
This is the Karen sword
art final technique!

137
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:04,125
I call it: Rising
Impact Infinity!

138
00:09:04,208 --> 00:09:07,458
[KIMITO] Your anime attack
names make no sense!

139
00:09:07,541 --> 00:09:12,500
[KAREN yelling]

140
00:09:15,791 --> 00:09:18,375
[AIKA]
She did it! It stopped moving!

141
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:22,000
[KAREN] Never mind about me.
Continue the fight.

142
00:09:23,291 --> 00:09:25,083
Kagurazaka?

143
00:09:25,166 --> 00:09:26,208
[KIMITO]
Thanks, Karen!

144
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:28,750
You can just keep
the jacket, 'kay?

145
00:09:32,875 --> 00:09:35,166
[MASAOMI]
Takemiya!

146
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:37,500
[TAKEMIYA]
Damn you, Masaomi!

147
00:09:39,708 --> 00:09:41,916
You have gotten much
stronger, my boy.

148
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:46,000
I'm not a little boy anymore,
old timer, I'm a man!

149
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:51,041
[BOTH yelling]

150
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:57,041
I hacked these two.

151
00:09:57,125 --> 00:09:58,458
Thanks, you're the best!

152
00:09:58,541 --> 00:09:59,416
[HAKUA]
Good luck.

153
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:00,583
[KIMITO yelps]

154
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:03,750
[KIMITO]
Oh boy.

155
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:21,458
Kimito. You came.

156
00:10:21,541 --> 00:10:23,083
[HOKO]
Well, well, well.

157
00:10:23,166 --> 00:10:25,375
If it isn't Reiko's
friend from school.

158
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:28,250
So nice to see you again.

159
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:29,375
I assume you've come here

160
00:10:29,458 --> 00:10:32,375
because you're concerned
for my daughter.

161
00:10:32,458 --> 00:10:34,833
But as you can
see, we're busy.

162
00:10:34,916 --> 00:10:38,250
So, I'm going to have to ask
you to leave right away.

163
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:41,916
Goodbye, sir. We
appreciate you stopping by.

164
00:10:43,416 --> 00:10:44,750
Uh, Ma'am?

165
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:45,791
Yes?

166
00:10:48,125 --> 00:10:50,333
I have something to say.

167
00:10:50,416 --> 00:10:52,208
The thing is-- Ah!

168
00:10:52,291 --> 00:10:54,666
I am against this marriage!

169
00:10:54,750 --> 00:10:56,541
Fly you fool.

170
00:10:56,625 --> 00:10:57,666
Is that so?

171
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:58,916
And so is your daughter!

172
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,416
My daughter is happy
to do her duty.

173
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:04,250
Isn't that right, love?
Tell your friend.

174
00:11:04,333 --> 00:11:05,458
She is nervous.

175
00:11:05,541 --> 00:11:07,416
But as a daughter of
the Arisugawa dynasty,

176
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,000
she knows exactly how
important this engagement is

177
00:11:10,083 --> 00:11:11,416
to our family legacy.

178
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:13,666
This isn't what Reiko
wants and you know it!

179
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:16,708
She's only going along with
it because she's afraid!

180
00:11:16,791 --> 00:11:18,750
It makes no difference
what the child wants.

181
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:19,958
[KIMITO gasps]

182
00:11:20,041 --> 00:11:23,083
Family comes first.
Even before true love.

183
00:11:23,166 --> 00:11:26,041
Reiko is fully aware that
this is a step she must take.

184
00:11:26,125 --> 00:11:29,250
And that to marry into a great
family is a noble calling.

185
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,625
Her desires notwithstanding,

186
00:11:30,708 --> 00:11:33,500
this is her sole
purpose in life.

187
00:11:33,583 --> 00:11:35,291
I know this is confusing.

188
00:11:35,375 --> 00:11:38,291
I wouldn't expect a mere
Commoner to understand.

189
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:47,458
[KIMITO]
You're right.

190
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:49,416
I've been at Seikain for
a little over a month,

191
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,708
and I still don't
understand your world.

192
00:11:51,791 --> 00:11:53,958
Not even a bit.

193
00:11:54,041 --> 00:11:55,250
Everything is different,

194
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:58,041
from the clothes you wear
to the food you eat.

195
00:11:58,125 --> 00:12:01,458
I did my best to explain what
life is like for regular people,

196
00:12:01,541 --> 00:12:03,750
but it doesn't get
through. Not really.

197
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:07,291
Honestly, I'm not sure we'll
ever understand each other.

198
00:12:07,375 --> 00:12:10,291
But, even so.

199
00:12:10,375 --> 00:12:11,708
All these girls...

200
00:12:11,791 --> 00:12:14,416
...the members of
the Commoner Club...

201
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,416
...they are my best friends!

202
00:12:21,666 --> 00:12:23,166
It's true.

203
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:25,500
So what if we do things
a little differently?

204
00:12:25,583 --> 00:12:28,458
So what if we come
from different places?

205
00:12:28,541 --> 00:12:30,666
We have had so much fun.

206
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:32,583
But now you're taking that away!

207
00:12:32,666 --> 00:12:34,125
You're tearing us apart!

208
00:12:34,208 --> 00:12:36,333
Stop! Please!

209
00:12:36,416 --> 00:12:38,208
[REIKO gasps]

210
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:40,166
He feels this strongly?

211
00:12:46,375 --> 00:12:47,708
That's quite a story.

212
00:12:47,791 --> 00:12:50,750
But Reiko's made her decision.
She's accepted her fate.

213
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:52,208
What a giant load of crap!

214
00:12:52,291 --> 00:12:53,416
Aika.

215
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,916
[gasps]

216
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,666
When I got to Seikain, I just
wanted people to like me.

217
00:12:57,750 --> 00:13:00,166
And all I cared about
was being popular.

218
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:03,333
But now I realize just
how shallow that was.

219
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:07,083
I mean. Who cares how
many friends you have?

220
00:13:07,166 --> 00:13:08,500
Life's not about
getting everyone

221
00:13:08,583 --> 00:13:09,750
to think you're awesome.

222
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:12,250
It's about finding the
people you click with.

223
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:16,625
I learned that from Kimito.
From Karen. From Hakua.

224
00:13:16,708 --> 00:13:19,000
But most of all, from Reiko!

225
00:13:19,083 --> 00:13:20,916
I know it's not our place
to barge into your house

226
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,750
and tell you what to do
with your own daughter,

227
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:26,625
even so... we're here!

228
00:13:26,708 --> 00:13:30,125
Because Reiko deserves to be
around the people she loves!

229
00:13:30,208 --> 00:13:32,083
Please don't force
her to marry him!

230
00:13:32,166 --> 00:13:34,208
We don't want to
lose our friend!

231
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:54,791
Please, ma'am!

232
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:55,958
[AIKA, HAKUA, KAREN]
Please, ma'am!

233
00:13:56,041 --> 00:13:57,250
Please, ma'am!

234
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:03,458
It's time for our
guests to leave now.

235
00:14:03,541 --> 00:14:04,875
[GUARD A]
Come with me.

236
00:14:04,958 --> 00:14:08,875
[AIKA] Let go! Kimito,
do something! Please!

237
00:14:08,958 --> 00:14:11,208
[KIMITO]
What can I do?

238
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:12,333
[REIKO]
Mother.

239
00:14:14,291 --> 00:14:17,250
I am sorry. But I'm
leaving home for good.

240
00:14:18,541 --> 00:14:19,625
Reiko.

241
00:14:19,708 --> 00:14:21,375
I appreciate your
sentiment, my darling,

242
00:14:21,458 --> 00:14:23,208
but do you even realize
what you're saying?

243
00:14:23,291 --> 00:14:24,791
Of course, I do!

244
00:14:24,875 --> 00:14:26,333
[HOKO]
So sure of yourself.

245
00:14:26,416 --> 00:14:28,291
I only ask because
I worry that perhaps

246
00:14:28,375 --> 00:14:30,875
you've forgotten
the way things work.

247
00:14:30,958 --> 00:14:32,958
Only young ladies from
prestigious families

248
00:14:33,041 --> 00:14:36,291
are given the honor
of attending Seikain.

249
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:38,375
If you walk away from
your family name, my dear,

250
00:14:38,458 --> 00:14:41,333
they won't so much as
let you in the front door.

251
00:14:41,416 --> 00:14:42,916
So if you want to
run away from home,

252
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,708
by all means, suit yourself.

253
00:14:44,791 --> 00:14:46,166
